  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Preheat</strong> the grill to high</p>\r\n<p><strong>Boil</strong> a kettle</p>\r\n<p><strong>Zest</strong> the lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;taking care not to include any white pith (which is very bitter)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Place</strong> the coconut cream sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> in a mug and cover with boiled water (this softens the naturally hard cream)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the rice, lime zest, 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> water and a pinch of salt to a pot with a lid over a high heat and bring to the boil</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> done, remove from the heat and keep covered until later</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Lato; font-size: 15px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">&nbsp;</span></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Cut</strong> the broccoli into quarters, lengthways</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cut</strong> each quarter again, so you end up with broccoli wedges&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Add</strong> the wedges to a baking tray (use tin foil to avoid mess)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Drizzle</strong> with vegetable oil and season generously with salt and pepper&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Put</strong> the tray directly under the grill and cook for 12-15 min or until nicely charred</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, pat the steaks dry with kitchen towel</p>\r\n<p><strong>Rub</strong> them with a little vegetable oil and season generously with salt on both sides</p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat until very hot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the steaks to the hot pan (in batches if needed) and cook for 1 min on each side (for medium-rare)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Transfer</strong> the cooked steaks to a plate and leave to rest</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reserve</strong> the pan for the next step&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Add</strong> the peanut butter, coconut cream, soy sauce and 1 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp]</span> sugar (brown, if you have it!) with 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> boiled water to the reserved pan</p>\r\n<p><strong>Whisk</strong> together (off the heat) until smooth</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> smooth, return the pan to a low heat and whisk until a sauce forms (approx. 3-4 min) then remove from the heat and set aside (it will thicken a little as it cools)</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, halve the lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> finely, discarding the root end<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Slice</strong> the steak as finely as you can (against the grain)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Cutting against the grain means identifying the natural lines in the steak and cutting in the opposite direction!</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/554.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Fluff</strong> the cooked rice, add the juice of half the <span class=\"text-danger\">[whole]</span> lime and season with salt and pepper</p>\r\n<p><strong>Spoon</strong> a pool of peanut sauce on to your plates and top with the sliced steak, serving the lime rice and charred broccoli to the side&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Garnish</strong> with spring onion and the remaining lime (cut into wedges)</p>",
      "order": 8,
